<item>
            <title>[HBASE-4769] Abort RegionServer Immediately on OOME</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4769</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, when the HRegionServer runs out of the memory, it will call master, which will cause more heap allocations and throw a second exception that it&apos;s run out of memory again. The easiest &amp;amp; safest way to avoid this OOME storm is to abort the RegionServer immediately when it hits the memory boundary.  Part of the 89-fb to trunk port.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12531063">HBASE-4769</key>
