                            <comment id="13148081" author="stack" created="Thu, 10 Nov 2011 22:52:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on patch (Fix &apos;itseft&apos; on commit).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Outside of this patch do we need to fix our &apos;abort&apos;?  Seems odd that we have &apos;abort&apos; and then this more radical &apos;abort&apos;, here its called &apos;forceAbort&apos;, where we call halt (Maybe we should have a &apos;halt&apos; method?  This patch would use it and I believe there is another halt call over in the distributed code?).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13148086" author="nspiegelberg" created="Thu, 10 Nov 2011 23:00:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like the other locations just call Runtime.getRuntime().halt(1) directly.  Maybe we should do the same?  BTW : Patch originally done by Liyin &amp;amp; reviewed by Kannan, so I&apos;m not 100% sure what their reasoning was.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
